dhanlen@beta.tricity.wsu.edu (Don A. Hanlen) writes:

>>3. for n := 52 downto 2
>>	 generate a random integer 'r' in the range 1..n 
>>	 swap array[r] <-> array[n]
>
>Let me ask, what is the probability that the card at the top of the deck
>(#52), will be at the top at the end of the shuffle?
>
>Answer:  0 (!)

Wrong. 'r' is in the range 1..n, not 1..n-1.  The top card will be swapped
with itself (i.e. not moved) with probability 1/52.

